This paper is about using word embeddings to improve sarcasm detection, which is a task related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves experimentation with different types of word embeddings, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of different feature sets, which could also place it in cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
